title: JSON Hypertext Application Language
description: This document proposes a media type for representing resources and their relations with hyperlinks. Full specification at https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-kelly-json-hal. Its root object MUST be a Resource Object.

Resource.title: Resource Object
Resource.description: A Resource Object represents a resource.

_links.title: _links contains links to other resources
_links.description: It is an object whose property names are link relation types (as defined by [RFC5988](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc5988)) and values are either a Link Object or an array of Link Objects. The subject resource of these links is the Resource Object of which the containing '_links' object is a property.

curies.title: HAL curies
curies.description: HAL establishes a mechanism called curies which allows for link relation types that are compact and more human readable, whilst still offering a way that they MAY be expanded into a dereferencable URI providing documentation.

_embedded.title: _embedded contains embedded resources
_embedded.description: It is an object whose property names are link relation types (as defined by [RFC5988](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc5988)) and values are either a Resource Object or an array of Resource Objects.

Link.title: Link Object
Link.description: A Link Object represents a hyperlink from the containing resource to a URI.

href.title: href
href.description: Its value is either a URI [RFC3986](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3986) or a URI Template [RFC6570](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6570). If the value is a URI Template then the Link Object SHOULD have a templated attribute whose value is true.

templated.title: templated
templated.description: Its value is boolean and SHOULD be true when the Link Object's href property is a URI Template. Its value SHOULD be considered false if it is undefined or any other value than true.

type.title: type
type.description: Its value is a string used as a hint to indicate the media type expected when dereferencing the target resource.

deprecation.title: deprecation
deprecation.description: Its presence indicates that the link is to be deprecated (i.e. removed) at a future date. Its value is a URL that SHOULD provide further information about the deprecation.

name.title: name
name.description: Its value MAY be used as a secondary key for selecting Link Objects which share the same relation type.

profile.title: profile
profile.description: Its value is a string which is a URI that hints about the profile (as defined by [RFC6906](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6906)) of the target resource.

title.title: title
title.description: Its value is a string and is intended for labelling the link with a human-readable identifier (as defined by [RFC5988](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc5988)).

hreflang.title: hreflang
hreflang.description: Its value is a string and is intended for indicating the language of the target resource (as defined by [RFC5988](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc5988)).

LinkRelationTypes.title: IANA Link Relation Types Registry
LinkRelationTypes.description: [RFC8288](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8288.html) Web Linking. This specification defines a model for the relationships between resources on the Web (links) and the type of those relationships (link relation types).

LanguageSubtags.title: IANA Language Subtag Registry
LanguageSubtags.description: [RFC5646](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5646.html) Language Subtag Registry. Only Subtags with Type: language are listed.

LocalPath.title: Regex for local (absolute or relative) path
